Hands-on Learning: Provides a practical introduction to key computer vision techniques such as face detection and image overlay using OpenCV, helping users deepen their understanding of real-time image processing.

Augmented Reality Foundation: Demonstrates fundamental AR concepts by augmenting live video feeds with virtual accessories, serving as a stepping stone for more advanced AR applications.

User Engagement: Enhances user interaction with live camera filters and toggling features, making the experience dynamic and interactive.

Customizability: Offers a flexible framework that can be easily extended to include additional filters, effects, or detection improvements, fostering creativity and experimentation.

Educational Tool: Useful for students, developers, and researchers to explore the integration of computer vision and multimedia applications in a straightforward and accessible manner.
